Vice President Biden congratulates President Juan Manuel Santos of Colombia for being awarded the 2016 Nobel Peace Prize. He commends Santos for his courage and dedication throughout the peace process and expresses admiration for his leadership. Biden acknowledges that although the Colombian people did not vote to ratify the peace agreement, they have not given up on the idea of peace and have an opportunity to strengthen the accord through a national dialogue. He encourages the people of Colombia to continue pursuing peace and assures that the United States will continue to support them on their journey. Biden also commits to personally supporting the Colombian people in building a new future.